Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.99,0:13:12.22,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,So, you got a copy \Nof the class roster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.22,0:13:13.10,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.59,0:13:15.21,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Let me start from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.67,0:13:18.14,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Did you hear that \NTakabayashi died?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.27,0:13:21.08,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,He had a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.45,0:13:23.70,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I know he had \Nheart problems, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.70,0:13:24.91,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.30,0:13:28.28,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The second June death \Nwas caused by illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:30.97,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,And when I got to school today,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.97,0:13:32.93,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,the whole class was acting weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.93,0:13:37.16,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,They acted as if I wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:40.59,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,So that's what they \Ndecided to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:44.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Does this mean I'm \Njust like you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.64,0:13:50.86,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,How does it feel to not exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.42,0:13:53.40,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Not so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:55.83,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,But in a way, it's a \Nload off my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.83,0:13:56.81,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:14:00.06,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Because now I \Nknow that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.31,0:14:08.27,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,This is where you live, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:09.31,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.31,0:14:11.86,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,But I thought you \Nalready figured this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.86,0:14:14.28,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You did say you \Nlived around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.28,0:14:15.98,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,And you're not a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.98,0:14:18.80,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Was that your mother \Nwho answered the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.74,0:14:21.27,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.27,0:14:25.50,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I very rarely get calls \Nfrom schoolmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.84,0:14:30.11,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Is Kirika your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.11,0:14:33.15,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Yes. I guess you'd \Ncall it a pseudonym.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.15,0:14:34.83,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She goes by Kirika.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.44,0:14:39.48,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,She's a strange woman who isolates herself in the studio upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.61,0:14:43.35,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So the "M" in "Studio M" \Nstands for Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.35,0:14:45.34,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It all makes sense \Nnow, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:50.98,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Let's go upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:05.47,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Did you know this was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.67,0:15:14.67,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.09,0:15:25.82,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Why don't you ask the questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:27.56,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It might be easier to \Nexplain everything that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.83,0:15:31.68,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I thought you hated \Nbeing questioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.68,0:15:34.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I do, but for today...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:37.53,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I'll make a special exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.89,0:15:41.29,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,First off, Misaki Mei...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:43.12,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,...you exist, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.12,0:15:46.12,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Did you think I was a ghost?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.12,0:15:47.21,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.72,0:15:50.09,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I guess you couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.50,0:15:52.79,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,But your doubts are \Ngone now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.79,0:15:57.30,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Now that you know I \Nexist as a living human.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.75,0:16:02.16,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I'm only nonexistent \Nto the others in class 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.96,0:16:04.44,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Since when?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.44,0:16:06.98,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It started on May 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.28,0:16:09.00,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,That's pretty recent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.17,0:16:13.80,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,A lot of things seemed strange to you from the start, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.48,0:16:16.63,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,And nobody would tell me why.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.15,0:16:22.39,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Not explaining the situation to you in the first place was a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.39,0:16:23.72,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:27.58,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,You were supposed to treat me \Nas someone who didn't exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.58,0:16:30.85,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,just like the rest of the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:35.15,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,But now, you're the same as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.15,0:16:36.55,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,How awful for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.85,0:16:39.68,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So they weren't bullying you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.05,0:16:42.52,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I don't think anyone \Nthought of it like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.58,0:16:50.91,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,I know that I no \Nlonger exist to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.91,0:16:52.94,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,but why are they doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.15,0:16:56.29,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That's the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.76,0:17:00.10,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Do you remember the story about the Misaki who died 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.10,0:17:00.95,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.30,0:17:04.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That was the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.13,0:17:07.66,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,After that, class 3 \Ndrew closer to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.19,0:17:09.33,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Death?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.33,0:17:16.42,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It happened to class 3 the year after Misaki's class graduated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.63,0:17:20.70,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,And, once it happens, once it begins,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.70,0:17:22.91,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,somebody dies each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.62,0:17:27.06,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Either a student, or \Nsomeone from their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.06,0:17:28.89,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,What is "it"?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.15,0:17:31.27,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's when...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.02,0:17:35.98,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,...the number of students \Nin the class increases by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.50,0:17:38.57,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Increases? So who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:41.57,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.15,0:17:47.44,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They can never figure out \Nwho the extra one is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:48.58,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,The extra one?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.44,0:17:57.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,25 years ago, shortly after the new term began, \Nthey realized that they were short one desk and chair.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.42,0:18:01.11,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Even though they had prepared enough for every student.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.83,0:18:04.89,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Couldn't they just check \Nthe school records?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.89,0:18:07.66,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It was useless. \NThey tried many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:11.59,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The roster and records had \Nbeen altered to be inconsistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.59,0:18:14.56,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They were just one \Ndesk and chair short.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.02,0:18:17.29,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So, someone rewrote the numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.29,0:18:19.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I used the word \N"altered" figuratively.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.13,0:18:23.25,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They say that everyone's \Nmemories had changed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.25,0:18:24.29,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:27.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Sounds impossible, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:31.62,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,But it's supposedly true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.20,0:18:36.93,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I was told this type of \Nphenomenon could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.51,0:18:38.89,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Phenomenon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.89,0:18:43.71,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,At first, they thought it was just an error and ignored it.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.71,0:18:49.86,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,But starting in April, people connected to the class started to die each month.{merge}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.86,0:18:51.02,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Each month?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.40,0:18:52.99,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,For the whole year?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.99,0:18:58.38,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That year, I think it was six \Nstudents and ten family members.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.38,0:19:00.27,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Clearly abnormal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.27,0:19:04.82,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,This phenomenon has \Ncontinued in class 3 ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.07,0:19:10.46,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So a ninth grader in class 3, \Nnamed Misaki, died 26 years ago.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.46,0:19:15.14,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,And the following year, there was an extra student in the class somehow.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.14,0:19:19.38,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,After which, people connected to \Nthe class started to die each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.24,0:19:23.75,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Why do people die when \Nthere's an extra student?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.70,0:19:26.31,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Nobody knows the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.31,0:19:28.03,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That's just what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.03,0:19:31.85,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Plus, that extra student is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.82,0:19:34.33,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,...someone dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.07,0:19:39.42,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,You mean the Misaki \Nwho died 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.86,0:19:45.86,Sign,Desk,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnJennifer's Hand Writing\blur0.4\alpha&H11&\fay-0.01\fax-0.9\pos(702,69)\frz340.016\c&H2D2320&}Who is \Ndead?{\alpha&HFF&}aa
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.46,0:19:45.31,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Is it... a ghost, or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.80,0:19:49.46,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,I think it's different from \Nwhat we'd call a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.46,0:19:51.62,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It seems to have a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.62,0:19:55.07,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,There's no way to tell it \Napart from the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.07,0:19:56.37,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,No way to tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:20:01.13,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That dead person has \Na soul and its memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.13,0:20:04.70,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and they don't \Nrealize they're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.38,0:20:07.49,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.49,0:20:10.28,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,The people connected to the class \Nwho have died over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.01,0:20:16.71,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,This is how I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:22.75,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Because of what class 3 did 26 years ago, \Nthe class is now a place that invites the dead.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.75,0:20:29.29,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,After that, the dead began to join the class and drew class 3 closer to death.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.15,0:20:32.42,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,In response,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.78,0:20:39.29,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,the students in class 3 came up with several "countermeasures" to try to escape this calamity.{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.98,0:20:41.90,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Like exorcisms?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.90,0:20:43.40,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Possibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.92,0:20:46.19,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They tried moving to \Na different classroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.19,0:20:49.53,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and changing the name \Nof class 3 to class C.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.53,0:20:52.20,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,But that didn't stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.20,0:20:55.60,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,So the problem is with the students in the ninth grade's third class?{merged}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.60,0:20:56.93,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Seems to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:01.11,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,Then, about ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.11,0:21:03.74,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,they found a way to \Ndeal with the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.28,0:21:09.45,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,A method that prevented \Npeople from dying each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.43,0:21:12.41,Default,Kouichi,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.95,0:21:17.41,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,They treat one student like they don't exist, to make up for the extra person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.91,0:21:21.42,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,That way, they return the \Nclass to its correct number,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.10,0:21:25.42,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,and they can avoid the \Ncalamity for that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.42,0:21:28.15,Default,Mei,0,0,0,,It's sort of like a charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.82,0:21:41.44,Sign,Kanji Title,0,0,0,,{\an8\b0\fscx100\fs40\fsp1\c&HF2F2F2&\blur0.6\pos(1089,564)}The Two
